"title": "6632: conviction",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6632",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The proving of a person guilty of sin or a crime. Scripture stresses that God has declared the guilt, together with its consequences, of sinful humanity. The term can also refer to a state of being convinced; i.e., the holding of a strong belief, especially a conscious awareness of one's guilt and the atoning death of Jesus Christ as the means of remission of that guilt.</p>\n<h2>Conviction is proving a person guilty of sin or a crime</h2>\n<h3>Proving someone guilty of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:46\">JHN 8:46</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:8-John16:9\">JHN 16:8–16:9</a> <em>NIV footnote at verse 8</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:24\">1CO 14:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:9\">JAS 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:15\">JUD 1:15</a></p>\n<h3>Proving someone guilty of a crime</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:15\">DEU 19:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:9\">EXO 22:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:3-Lev17:4\">LEV 17:3–17:4</a>NUM <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev35:30\">35:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:6\">DEU 17:6</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:13\">2SA 14:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:10\">PSA 5:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:7\">PSA 109:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:25\">PRO 24:25</a>LUK <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:4\">23:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:14\">LUK 23:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:22\">LUK 23:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:38\">JHN 18:38</a>ACT <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John24:13\">24:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts25:7\">ACT 25:7</a></p>\n<h2>God's conviction of sinful humanity</h2>\n<h3>He declares them to be guilty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:19-Rom3:20\">ROM 3:19–3:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:9\">PSA 5:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:7\">PSA 10:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps14:1-Ps14:3\">PSA 14:1–14:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps53:1-Ps53:3\">PSA 53:1–53:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps140:3\">PSA 140:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:20\">ECC 7:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:7-Isa59:8\">ISA 59:7–59:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:10-Rom3:18\">ROM 3:10–3:18</a></p>\n<h3>He also declares the consequences of their guilt</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:17\">GEN 2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:17-Gen3:19\">GEN 3:17–3:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:32\">ROM 1:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:12\">ROM 5:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:16-Rom5:19\">ROM 5:16–5:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:22\">1CO 15:22</a></p>\n<h2>Conviction as holding a strong belief</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:5\">ROM 14:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:28\">GEN 45:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:20\">MAT 17:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:6\">LUK 20:6</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:26\">MAT 21:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:32\">MRK 11:32</a> <em>The people were convinced that John was a prophet</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:31\">LUK 16:31</a>ACT <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:4\">17:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:26\">ACT 19:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:24\">ACT 28:24</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:9\">ACT 26:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:26\">ACT 26:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:19\">ROM 2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:21\">ROM 4:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:38-Rom8:39\">ROM 8:38–8:39</a> <em>Paul's conviction that it is impossible to be separated from God's love</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:14\">ROM 14:14</a> <em>Paul's personal convictions about food regulations</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:14\">ROM 15:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:14\">2CO 5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:25\">PHP 1:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:5\">1TH 1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:5\">2TI 1:5</a> <em>Paul is convinced by Timothy's faith</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:12\">2TI 1:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:14\">2TI 3:14</a></p>\n<h2>Conviction as the conscious awareness of one's guilt</h2>\n<h3>Examples of conviction not resulting in repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:27\">EXO 9:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:16\">EXO 10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:40\">NUM 14:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:34\">NUM 22:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:41\">DEU 1:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:101\">JDG 10:101</a>SA <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg15:24\">15:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:17\">1SA 24:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:21\">1SA 26:21</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:3-Matt27:4\">MAT 27:3–27:4</a> <em>Judas Iscariot</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:25\">ACT 24:25</a> <em>Governor Felix</em></p>\n<h3>Examples of conviction leading to repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:37\">ACT 2:37</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:13\">2SA 12:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:3-Ps51:4\">PSA 51:3–51:4</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:75\">MAT 26:75</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:72\">MRK 14:72</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:62\">LUK 22:62</a> <em>Peter</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:17-Luke15:18\">LUK 15:17–15:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:21\">LUK 15:21</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:30\">ACT 16:30</a> <em>the Philippian jailer</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:9\">ROM 7:9</a></p>",
